<style>
  .auto-submit-indicator {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  .auto-submit-indicator svg {
    transform: rotate(-90deg);
  }
  .progress-ring {
    /* Smooth out the tiny increments */
    transition: stroke-dashoffset 10ms linear;
  }
</style>

<script type="module">
  const form = document.getElementById('cmsFormAutoSubmit');
  const circle = document.getElementById('loaderCircle');
  
  const circumference = 2 * Math.PI * 8; // ~50.26
  const WAIT_TIME = 800; // Total countdown time in ms
  
  let startTime;
  let rafId;

  function updateCircle(timestamp) {
    if (!startTime) startTime = timestamp;
    const elapsed = timestamp - startTime;
    const progress = Math.min(elapsed / (WAIT_TIME + 200), 1);
    
    // Calculate offset: Full (50.26) to Empty (0)
    // To make it "grow", we subtract progress from circumference
    const offset = circumference - (progress * circumference);
    circle.style.strokeDashoffset = offset;

    if (elapsed < WAIT_TIME) {
      rafId = requestAnimationFrame(updateCircle);
    } else {
      // Countdown finished
      form.requestSubmit();
      resetCircle();
    }
  }

  function startCountdown() {
    resetCircle();
    rafId = requestAnimationFrame(updateCircle);
  }

  function resetCircle() {
    cancelAnimationFrame(rafId);
    startTime = null;
    circle.style.strokeDashoffset = circumference;
  }

  // Handle Checkbox/Buttons
  form.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
    if (event.target.type === "button" || event.target.type === "checkbox") {
      startCountdown();
    }
  });

  // Handle Typing/Input
  form.addEventListener('input', () => {
    startCountdown();
  });
</script>

<script type="module">
  const form = document.getElementById('cmsFormAutoSubmit');
  // Submit on click on a checkbox button
  form.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
    if (event.target.type == "button") {
      setTimeout(() => {
        form.requestSubmit();
      })
    }
  });

  // Submit on typing
  let timeoutId;
  form.addEventListener('input', (event) => {
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => {
      form.requestSubmit();
    }, 500)
  })
</script>

  .members-sort-icon-unchecked, .members-sort-icon-checked {
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    margin-right: 8px; /* Space between icon and text */
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  /* Default state: Show unchecked, hide checked */
  .members-sort-icon-checked {
    display: none;
    fill: #007bff; /* Blue color for checked */
  }
  .members-sort-icon-unchecked {
    display: block;
    fill: #ccc; /* Gray color for unchecked */
  }

  /* CHECKED State: Swap the icons */
  /* When input is checked, find the sibling SVG with class .members-sort-icon-unchecked and hide it */
  .members-sort-checkbox input:checked ~ .members-sort-icon-unchecked {
    display: none;
  }
  /* When input is checked, find the sibling SVG with class .members-sort-icon-checked and show it */
  .members-sort-checkbox input:checked ~ .members-sort-icon-checked {
    display: block;
  }
</style>

<style>
  .smoke-particle {
    position: absolute;
    pointer-events: none;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(245, 245, 245, 0.8) 0%, rgba(100, 100, 100, 0.1) 70%);
    z-index: 9999;
    will-change: transform, opacity;
  }
</style>
<script>
  (function() {
    // We attach listeners to the document to handle elements added dynamically (Webstudio hydration)
    document.addEventListener('mouseover', (e) => {
      const target = e.target.closest('.rocket-link');
      if (!target || target._isSmoking) return; // Prevent double triggers
      
      const rocket = target.querySelector('.rocket-icon');
      if (!rocket) return;

      clearTimeout(target._stopTimeout);
      target._isSmoking = true;
      loop(rocket, target);
    });

    document.addEventListener('mouseout', (e) => {
      const target = e.target.closest('.rocket-link');
      if (!target || target.contains(e.relatedTarget)) return; 
      target._isSmoking = false;
      cancelAnimationFrame(target._animFrame);
    });

    function loop(rocket, container) {
      if (!container._isSmoking) return;
      for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) spawn(rocket);
      container._animFrame = requestAnimationFrame(() => loop(rocket, container));
    }

    function spawn(el) {
      const rect = el.getBoundingClientRect();
      if (rect.width === 0) return; // invisible element check

      const w = window;
      const cx = rect.left + rect.width / 2 + w.scrollX;
      const cy = rect.top + rect.height / 2 + w.scrollY;

      const mat = new WebKitCSSMatrix(getComputedStyle(el).transform);
      const angle = Math.atan2(mat.b, mat.a) + 2.356; // +135deg to find tail
      const offset = rect.width * 0.4;

      const div = document.createElement('div');
      div.className = 'smoke-particle';
      document.body.appendChild(div);

      const jitter = angle + 0.35 * (Math.random() - 0.5);
      const speed = Math.random() * 4 + 2;
      
      let x = (cx - 4) + Math.cos(angle) * offset;
      let y = cy + Math.sin(angle) * offset;
      let vx = Math.cos(jitter) * speed;
      let vy = Math.sin(jitter) * speed;
      let op = 1;
      const sizeBase = Math.random() * 4 + 4;

      (function anim() {
        x += vx;
        y += vy;
        vx *= 0.95;
        vy *= 0.95;
        op -= 0.02;

        if (op <= 0) return div.remove();

        div.style.left = x + 'px';
        div.style.top = y + 'px';
        div.style.opacity = op;
        div.style.width = div.style.height = sizeBase + 'px';
        div.style.transform = `scale(${2 + (2 - 2 * op)})`; // Growth effect

        requestAnimationFrame(anim);
      })();
    }
  })();
</script>

BSLI IREC Project team competes annually in Texas

Every year, this team travels to Texas to compete in the International Rocket Engineering Competition, the largest intercollegiate rocketry competition. The team competes in the 30K Student Research and Designed (SRAD) category, meaning they must design and build a rocket that can reach an altitude of 30,000 feet.
This team competes at the International Rocket Engineering Competition, hosted annually in Texas. BSLI competes in the 30k Student Research and Developed (SRAD) category.
BSLI Liquids team focuses on liquid bipropellant rocket engine development. Current development includes working towards test firing an LR-101, and further refining our 1st custom engine.
